to_reference":"AcnlKN0lCCWbwHQiyPZ2-8E_cZxn9sZUlmCYygqlGoS1DivbQwGLzC1dZneUIATvYwNaWpm2_Z_TwEKVf00oD2Wc3JRfcFUSwgvWpePTeB2ifmV3Jld1JWjLg-rA0IYOCmRMOlN2zKCPpAZMb8_WBen1UdsOPlKza1986czXei5h7rtjmUnuRPGUYWDJLskAW-SIGzAVLi5rpXmsG15nK8kVrpwjjg4gZ3HA7BCWYcJHic40AtowvFqwskqRsp8vEnrntx9e7OBVwJdoNflyH0iaS8zDAuAmvmqUNZqNOFoQ0qoiBw","width":1323,"height":829,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/111964297956402137879\">Sagarlore Hotela</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN1dfVCS_UGbRw073-lnX99GqAvMI-F6Q927ZgDo1QVupN6BjucqUpmTvOy5rX_0FsQBw853g_IWjdp9eaMMzk0qDDWMvh3gbgwlmrZHzqSMHXvG2uUyUskOWYVhct2obW7jtX1dTAs1JD1tPraciorxVK2gh9id-1g3luP2Fi2GFyiH7uNi90lDlQHG_nVYvvSYEivB9ZR9DSxpEWhA6KiqN1CN6xmPfH4LpKdARXUa7mF3QXymrDQ9bQ-CO0p_o7zHZD-YmLUDi3uCxF5CyXAcbEzeVuJGweInnuPSGwDcpg","width":2988,"height":3984,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/111964297956402137879\">Sagarlore Hotela</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Simon dk","rating":3,"text":"We booked for two nights, stayed one. We were unable to open windows as the grounds of the ''hotel'' which is more of a guest house, were infested with shield bugs which came into the room. We only had the windows open half an hour and about 50 of them came in and had to be thrown out. The room was simple and a bit sparse. Certainly not good enough for what they were charging. For the same costs you can book a proper hotel with appropriate standards if interior and quality. The aircon unfortunately was an all or nothing type so we either were hot or freezing air straight onto the bed. The bathroom drains were an issue with a bad smell of sewage all night. We mentioned this all the following morning as the reason we were not staying. Unfortunately the receptionist had to inform the owners regarding any offer of compensation etc. needless to say as we had to apy upfront, no offer has been forthcoming.\nThat said, credit where it is due, the lady re receptionist who also did most everything else around the place, was excellent, friendly, efficient. The breakfast was set out on each table rather than a buffet due to lack.of room in the place but was good quality.  Its just a shame the accomodation we were given was not fit for purpose and the owners not very savvy re customer satisfaction. As I understand it, its owned by the same people who own the local cider mill and two restaurants. It doesnt seem they feel the need to be competative re price or sensitaive about reputation. If you are looking for something local you can get far better for less elsewhere.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Birce Gokalp","rating":3,"text":"Location was not great, it is close to a motorway. We thought it would have been easier to get to town with public transport. But you have to walk 15 mins to get the bus and buses are every 20 mins. If you are planning to use your car all the time, then it is only a 10 minute drive to San Sebastian. Compared to other hotels we stayed in the area, it was also expensive for the quality.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Max Hope","rating":5,"text":"Amazing!! Very nice treatment. Local products for sale at good prices. You feel relaxed the moment you enter the hotel. The pool is nice and clean.  Breakfast is definitely worth taking. Would recommend 10/10 and will return.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Bastien Francois","rating":4,"text":"Nice, quite, simple fonctional rooms, in the middle of the countryside, close to the city. Perfect.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"R Crane","rating":5,"text":"My husband and I found this place while looking for a hotel just outside of San Sebastian. It''s like a 7 minute drive from San Sebastian and it was a perfect stay. We adored the friendly staff, our beautiful quiet room, our wonderful and probably best breakfast we had in Spain. They served us a whole bottle of the juice made at the Petritegi cidery and it was so delicious, we bought some for the road. Highly recommend a stay here.","time":"a year ago"}]':