jsonb, '[{"author":"Monica Constain","rating":5,"text":"It’s only been a week from our wedding, and I already can’t wait to go back. It sounded like a cliché when people said their wedding day was the best day of their lives, but ours truly was. Finca El Campillo is the most gorgeous and magical place, and I feel incredibly blessed that we got to celebrate our wedding here. From the setting to the staff, the service, the food, the vibes… it was all perfect. Huge thank you to everyone who made this day unforgettable, not only to us, but also to our friends and family. We will be back soon ","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Jody Bandremer","rating":5,"text":"We were guests at a wedding at this magical venue. It was a combination of a castle and elegant farmhouse in a picturesque and expansive park setting. The staff didn''t bat an eye when the event had to transition indoors due to weather. They were attentive, the food was delicious, the decor was elegant and warm. I especially fell in love with the table settings and glassware.... elegant! After dinner we transitioned to another area across the property for an after dinner disco party where the music was engaging, drinks were flowing and the dessert/candy table was set up so beautifully and delicious!  Highly recommend Finca El Campillo!","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Eduardo Fernandes","rating":5,"text":"This was the best of the best! Attending a wedding at this 13th-century castle, once the hunting lodge of the King of Spain, was an unforgettable experience. The historical atmosphere and the stunning architecture, along with the panoramic views, created a magical setting. The staff were incredibly professional and attentive, ensuring everything ran smoothly. The blend of rich history and modern amenities provided the perfect backdrop for such a special day. As a guest, I couldn''t have imagined a more enchanting venue. Highly recommended!","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"melissa fernandez","rating":5,"text":"I attended a wedding here a few years back and it was honestly the most magical, picture perfect wedding I have ever attended. The  grounds are a natural haven and the service was top notch- everything was truly spectacular.","time":"9 months ago"},{"author":"Mary Palacio-Pike","rating":5,"text":"Our family spent a few days at El Campillo this past Christmas and all I can say is that I fell in love with again with its peaceful yet exciting environment. We enjoyed great walks framed by amazing beauty. The cuisine and service hasn’t been matched yet while in Spain. The attention to detail and willingness to please makes you feel like royalty in your own castle. I definitely look forward to coming back for more.","time":"3 years ago"}]'::jsonb,
