e’ve ever stayed. The Belle-Époque architecture adds a sense of grandeur and history, yet the interiors are modern, elegant, and supremely comfortable.\n\nThe rooms were spacious, beautifully appointed, and immaculately maintained, with balconies that opened up to the stunning lake. The staff were exceptional—warm, professional, and attentive.  The special touch of the surprise that was left for us at the room because we were also celebrating a special day. The breakfast was great as well and everything combined it made the experience truly remarkable.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Hema Rupnarain","rating":5,"text":"We stayed at the Fairmont for our first visit to Montreux to experience the Christmas Market. We were a family of 4, with two children ages 5 and 7. We felt very welcome and the amenities and service were amazing. They provided a welcome gift for our two little girls, and one for us as well which was a very nice surprise. The room was gorgeous and provided an incredible view of Lake Geneva. The breakfast buffet was outstanding, and service was very attentive there as well.\n\nThe hotel is conveniently located close to bus stops, the train station, and Montreux Noel. We were able to walk almost anywhere. When we come to Montreux in the future, the Fairmont will be our first choice. Thank you for a wonderful stay!","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Campbell C","rating":5,"text":"Exceptional service and beautifully renovated rooms. We had a great view from our lake view room. This hotel exceeds the high standards set by the fairmont brand and the amex fhr program. The breakfast was excellent with lots of options and a great view.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Go Experiences","rating":5,"text":"We had a perfect stay: our room had 3 balconies with the breathtaking view over Lac Léman and Montreux Riviera! Breakfast is a treat and cuisine and Montreux Jazz Cafe is delicious! We loved the Spa - it was perfect for relaxation and pampering! Location is fantastic, just steps away from the Christmas Market, which is so convenient!","time":"a month ago"}]'::jsonb,
