655889904\">Hôtel Beau-Rivage Palace</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN1dKSfw2x3382WH4rboWPdgSGIam1imgMe46C13v8eKBf4inlgYJ9x37Yd_APy_Xc51pDgcrntktWlTSTY5wrl8vHN3m_arc0KB4Dbmk1NRljaqn8EWxSP4nwBjtLaSqgQNjmDdRF4y6ysVqk5McFF5ibaY_9DfvCMgAOVXgfIt43FXZClMgG6DeFcP2KVuIvxlA2eKIqBI6h5t6einKR57ZiUBGmtLbBLOyaJrbtVP4-ao88Go07nHzZksfa2Nlhj0xYmBd8_B9TyjmrvQILhC7iu5Fo_EPojeyoT6fyDOXQ","width":2048,"height":1365,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/100804624076655889904\">Hôtel Beau-Rivage Palace</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0T6j6W0oP8kV4fkoIGIKs9DLuGSUIz4UCKOZZj14rdiHghHKI7CR2NXoZbmg9RrzLUPYEJS6WvUAvyFPqz_0f7pFbR4eTjaYoFEam7yORSRALbcC46WJjmBtu6Viaaew6iBEgOrKr1t8MPD9Dc7tnSB1fPtn6pXz843PFk4zcy-biMy3MmYAHb1D2JfzC6oZUGF-pNv3aE4RW6CmfALGNPqe8sQQdFUKR74KtSXrftcmjNbEO48vMtztHw3bZatjC1i6rI_hOJIKxywXTpt9Pej-hC-rhjP6YzVZG5hsKPvg","width":3200,"height":4800,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/100804624076655889904\">Hôtel Beau-Rivage Palace</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Ольга К","rating":5,"text":"An unforgettable experience that stays with you\n\nOur stay at the Beau-Rivage Palace was truly magical and unforgettable. From the very first moments, I felt surrounded by care and attention — every detail was thoughtfully considered and perfectly executed. The warm welcome with gifts and the incredibly touching handwritten welcome letter meant so much to us. It conveyed a sense of genuine appreciation and warmth, something truly rare nowadays.\n\nThe room was spacious and elegant, featuring a walk-in wardrobe, a beautiful bathroom, and a large balcony with breathtaking views over Lake Geneva. The room included a king-size bed and a sofa, offering absolute comfort. All in-room amenities were by Guerlain, which perfectly reflects the exceptional level of attention to guests and makes the stay even more special.\n\nReturning to the hotel felt like stepping into a fairytale, a place where kings and queens once lived. A destination with a remarkable history, created with great care and passion. The feeling of staying in a living museum is simply priceless.\n\nA special pleasure was the Guerlain boutique located directly inside the Palace, offering everything from refined gifts and iconic fragrances to elegant evening gowns. This rare combination of luxury, taste, and convenience makes everything exceptional easily accessible.\n\nOur child was absolutely delighted — she spent almost two hours in the kids’ club, surrounded by care and attention, and did not want to leave. Seeing her so happy was incredibly touching.\n\nThe hotel grounds are stunning, and the views of Lake Geneva are truly unforgettable. Dinner at the Michelin-starred restaurant was a genuine culinary revelation — luxurious, refined, with flawless presentation. A true celebration of taste. The entire Palace is beautifully decorated with fresh orchids, creating an atmosphere of refined elegance.\n\nBreakfast was another highlight, offering an incredible variety of dishes and more than 12 freshly pressed juices. The spa is simply exceptional — a place to fully relax both body and mind.\n\nThe hotel also offers tennis courts, golf facilities, a children’s playground, and beautiful relaxation areas. This experience was truly unforgettable.\n\nThank you from the bottom of our hearts — we will definitely return.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Ian Macdonald","rating":5,"text":"Very impressive decorations for Christmas. Staff in the restaurant at breakfast were very helpful and friendly. The bar in which we had aperitifs was pleasant with excellent staff. The Michelin starred restaurant was excellent with very efficient, friendly staff.\nChecking in to the hotel was a little slow, but once I got to the front of the queue the staff were very efficient and helpful","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Matteo Daldini","rating":5,"text":"We were at beau rivage palace for a short stay of 2 nights and we were amazed by the quality that this hotel has to offer. Starting from the check-in, were the young staff of receptionists welcomed us warmly and were happy to help us for any kind of situation, to the room and bathroom design and comfort level (yes, the beds are very very comfortable).\n\nThe old wing of the hotel is like a museum with his historic photography, portraits, old documents, historical meeting rooms and the most ancient elevator in Switzerland. We could also get a tour with some explanation of the hotel’s historical background which was provided by Jean Charles, who also assisted us during our whole stay. Thank you very much!\n\nWe could enjoy the guerlain spa as well. The spa itself isn’t that big, but if you consider that it is built inside an historic building like this, they did a really good job. The modern design is perfectly integrated with the old building. The pools as well as the changing rooms are perfectly clean all the time. This is a place you surely want to go to relax after a walking day or sport.\n\nThe hotel staff is amazing, very attentive to help the guests but also very discrete. This we must say again and again. These guys go above and beyond for the hotel guest (and not only). They make you want to come back!  We hope we can be back soon.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Robin Prause","rating":5,"text":"Magnificent ! Stayed for two nights and enjoyed every second. Brasserie and the Japanese Restaurant Kaigan were very good. Breakfast outstanding with the best pastry I''ve ever had in a 5* Hotel in Switzerland. All staff is exceptionally attentive and professional. Beau Rivage Palace definitely stands out in the family of Swiss Deluxe Hotels. Merci Beaucop!","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Arwa Al-nassar","rating":4,"text":"The overall experience was really good! The receptionists were very nice and welcoming. The view and our rooms were excellent ,clean, spacious, and very comfortable.\n\nHowever, the elevator was not working due to maintenance, and the main stairs were also closed. We had to use the service elevator, which guests didn’t have access to, so one of the receptionists had to escort us to our room each time. This was not acceptable for such a prestigious hotel, especially since there was no alternative elevator available.\n\nAdditionally, the breakfast service was quite slow, and we had to wait a long time to be served.\n\nOverall, despite these issues, we still enjoyed our stay.","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
