wMw9wu3_t6y_40ynB_aUOO6VQBhKury4T5MrtIJSY7vnNdw8MBczr9CHYwM5KzwqsHgYhWoOJsxBy84wTVEiYQITZdrk7zVn2SYoOrcZMJR14rPqD_8HBsL2Tj60uYU8W3haDZj6-Z40mO_yTO1woeog6EPR2QaLxPmpF-sqm3-gbdScqj_u5gwlvVQTf3YKUU9A9k4L91a0gQwPZqLpw2SA44twj_WYVI7w0JDduwemG_YNKCB9gAI5NeODK_37HX5bnppGYK_ZD7rkw","width":2048,"height":1401,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/104507141117116107004\">Hotel Royal Savoy Lausanne</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2NxL4MB8pk9YaV-ml2xooQKSUGrG7EVIDolO7U2-SPl2WZl2iCculJnKeAbTwbFKG-LXBuX-qWUnW225zGird7ORhDuofKa7yGyrHGaeAqhEc32svZuSwejtWdHNdm0opHogJ3PaR3RP90x4_JdQe_TUcsTz0G7Og8mlxVb9JHGx1ht_qYKL7yZQz0BStnVY2OoV284nUoQPUTa9Ys_OHWuQFdOKlNn36rkRCsVuaMEV1auNRv7P-V1c9xgN-FvIyNmE7GRQQcaXVtXdEoXKtcTxemuWdbj3Rrpcck4Cq40ET8EAtVUUGnBlcVwCKbStzDHg2RDNJCrm_T5iZQmkx-5I5x94VldY5QdVJdqrIdugz0HrLrXOcYiOWgrgvk_14PSxM454ThEWLTToIlqpUK1YWWdX_7YqhyifyondE","width":4032,"height":3024,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/101252818736611926253\">Alex R.</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"AP deB","rating":5,"text":"Stayed on business for two nights. Probably the most grand hotel in Lausanne. Very friendly and helpful staff and an excellent room, cannot fault. Room service very pricey and very average food. That seems to be a pattern in Switzerland though so not an issue with the hotel as such. Breakfast was however very good - especially the bacon.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Jamila M","rating":5,"text":"Honestly, we couldn''t be more happy with the service, facilities, location, exterior/interior design, staff flexibility, spa... pretty everything.\nOur personal thank you to all the personnel, you are all not just top-notch trained but genuinely kind and helpful by nature. We felt like home, thank you to you.\nCannot recommend staying in this hotel enough, only high words and happy feelings.\nFrom the family of 5 (from adults, teens to baby).","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"06hta","rating":4,"text":"The hotel is a beautiful building and the rooms are much more spacious and better equipped with automatic bidets, good sized TVs and over looking a beautiful view. The concierge staff are incredible and have been nothing but polite and helpful. The restaurant staff however.. are another story. Some incidents I will not share as they have been resolved however in our last day my children went down 15mins before the closing of breakfast which was at 10:15 (closing is 10:30) and every time they would ask to be served the waiter would tell them “ 5 more minutes” and before you knew it it was 10:33 and when they finally asked the waiter for a third time he responded “sorry we close at 10:30” and what my children wanted was something out of the cold section of the buffet and not freshly cooked food. There is no excuse for this apart from bad taste from the waiter who must have gotten away with this type of behavior several times otherwise he wouldn’t have dared to do this to paying customers at a 5 star hotel in Switzerland! This in my opinion is grounds for firing. The day before that we were finishing our breakfast and it was past 10:30 and the waitress was pulling the plate mat from u see my wife’s plat in an attempt to get us to finish our meal fast so they can prepare for lunch. Either we have an issue with culture shock or this hotels restaurant staff need to learn some customer service tips and maybe some general manners!\n\nOther wise, aside from the breakfast experience, the hotel and its staff were excellent. The rooms were spotless and the linens were as clean as can be. The pool is a bit small but does the job. The garden is lovely. I would definitely recommend this hotel .","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Michael Dower","rating":5,"text":"From start to finish, this hotel was exceptional. All the staff were incredible and nothing was too much trouble.  We really enjoyed our stay and would highly recommend.\n\nOnly minor criticism, I would have expected the SPA and pool area to be adults only. Suggestion, make a separate family/kids pool.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Yousef J.H","rating":5,"text":"I had the pleasure of staying at the Hôtel Royal Savoy Lausanne for two nights in one of their suites, and it was a truly exceptional experience. This elegant hotel exudes timeless sophistication, blending classic charm with modern luxury. The suite was a highlight—spacious, well-appointed, and designed with meticulous attention to detail, offering a comfortable and stylish retreat after a day of exploring Lausanne.\nThe service was nothing short of outstanding. From the warm welcome at check-in to the attentive staff throughout my stay, every interaction was professional yet genuinely friendly, making me feel valued and well-cared for. The amenities, from the serene spa to the exquisite dining options, elevated the experience further, with every detail thoughtfully curated.\nThe location is also a major plus, perfectly situated for both leisure and business travelers, with easy access to Lausanne’s key attractions. The suite’s decent size provided ample space to relax, and the overall ambiance of the hotel created a perfect balance of luxury and comfort. I highly recommend the Hôtel Royal Savoy Lausanne for anyone seeking a refined and memorable stay in this beautiful city!","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
