d not in the empty spaces available, terrace was smokey, and the overpriced food was subpar (artichoke and filet de perche were both tough).","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Toronto Time OUT","rating":5,"text":"As someone stays in 5star hotels every week, I say this is one of the best experiences. Room is in a belle epoch style, warm and has its own history. It’s not like modern generic hotel rooms that all look the same. My room has an open terrace that allows you see Lac Léman and the Mountain View. I can hear the birds sing in the morning.\nStaffs are professional, helpful and attentive, and here I experience the true hospitality.\nRestaurant offers healthy and delicious food and wine collection.\nLocation is top. Next to the promenade. And a bus stop.","time":"8 months ago"},{"author":"Brian Odom","rating":3,"text":"Nice hotel with helpful staff. But their key arrangement with the family suite does not make sense. The suite sleeps a couple plus a child. (Our child is 12, so independent.) However, they will only give two keys. It would normally be OK to leave keys at the front desk so all three of us can go in and out independently. But the door to the suite is old-style, such that you need a key to lock or unlock it, even if you are inside. So, if two people want to go out independently, they have the choice of either leaving the room unlocked, or locking the third person in the room.","time":"6 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
