2mw9PFhn8gfB2GYJm1D5GKq0gS0AjZH_Er23sMEqPlsGDgI-fx7kr2MYfxkD0QA7qXBRUZ5eaq8ns4kYbG3VoIU4rEkUjQ58dYzcJg","width":2592,"height":3872,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/117946116240952854820\">Hotel Château Gütsch</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN17Q-i-raEjLLb0mjT4nR9fejXy_S2kzCIgbGBvBFQQ69b5LS-Kr2YO-1gKIV_PaV0l1FsAsIwbguOX8isJa8k3LFV0cW4ByGswLnQsVe6V70qsXx_QhWEqdMS89Z1ovjP1E1yrLR7UPkpHvZ89ErcEMtUCXa645HbTeGXjHjE4BfTdWUPAAUh_STGpxVpKKZ5B7fU_gD8Rt9EGucSUbfBHmnQm9I4lTLsrOFERHN_n7Lbk823s0ujn6oj9ov_Kahy-oqiZ-KQy7sIZkSgJKl7_W2-h8Dq9KEE1RA1MR1pNqw","width":4800,"height":1963,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/117946116240952854820\">Hotel Château Gütsch</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Martina","rating":5,"text":"I have been visiting the bar at Château Gütsch for many years now, and every time I return, I am reminded why it remains one of my favourite places in Luzern. From the moment you step inside, the atmosphere feels both elegant and welcoming — a beautiful blend of classic charm and relaxed comfort. The staff are consistently outstanding, always greeting guests with genuine warmth and professionalism. What sets this bar apart is the way the team goes the extra mile without ever being intrusive. They pay attention to every detail, make thoughtful recommendations, and somehow manage to make each visit feel personal.\n\nThe cocktails here are truly exceptional. The bartenders are talented and creative, offering beautifully balanced drinks that are full of flavour and presented with care. Even the non-alcoholic cocktails are impressive — refreshing, imaginative, and crafted with the same level of artistry as the signature drinks. It’s rare to find a place where every option on the menu feels special, but Château Gütsch achieves exactly that.\n\nWhether you’re celebrating an occasion or simply enjoying a quiet night out, the bar is the perfect setting for a romantic evening. With stunning views over Luzern, cosy lighting, and a refined atmosphere, it creates unforgettable moments every time. I cannot recommend it highly enough.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Alberto Arzú","rating":5,"text":"This is an outstanding mixology bar with an even more impressive view. Overlooking the city of Lucerne, guests are welcomed by a warm, attentive staff who genuinely elevate the experience. The bar offers an excellent selection of wines, sparkling wines, beers, spirits, and cocktails. Be sure to try their house twists on classic cocktails, as well as their original creations. The ambiance, paired with the panoramic view, is a truly delightful enhancement, and prices are very reasonable by Swiss standards.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Lauren Snodgrass","rating":5,"text":"From check in to check out it was a wonderful stay. Staff was friendly and helpful. We were offered water and prosecco upon arrival. Parking was right in front of the hotel and 20CHF. The rooms….I can’t imagine a more beautiful view. Included in our stay was the mini bar and little snacks left for us.\nThe American Bar had wonderful craft cocktails and the food was good as well. Breakfast was typical buffets with meats, cheeses, pastries and yogurt with the option to order eggs. A little pricey at 39CHF in my opinion, but very convenient . The lift down to the Main Street is perfect and everything is walkable from there however they did offer a free bus pass with the stay. Would recommend highly!","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Kent Wang","rating":5,"text":"The bar has incredible terrace overlooking the city. Good cocktails. Food is decent, with burgers and snacks, but not a full restaurant\n\nThe restaurant also has good views, but its terrace was closed during low season.\n\nGo via the Gütschbahn","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Ben Bouckley","rating":3,"text":"Decidedly average and mediocre for the money. Visited two years ago and it was fab. This time around we had a room with a mezzanine - as we visited with our six year-old son - and it was a shabby, cramped  motel-style affair, with some battered old furniture that isn’t consistent with the claimed class of this hotel. No kettle - tea/coffee in the room.\n\nOverall, we noticed that the hotel was dirtier and more down at heel compared to our previous visit and in need of renovation. My wife and I revisited the much-vaunted cocktail bar and were simply ignored, even though it wasn’t busy. We were barely acknowledged on entry and sat down at a table full of empty glasses, then waited, and waited… 100 Great Gatsby-themed party flyers, but nary a sign of a cocktail menu or the barman. We noticed that the floor was dirty.\n\nWe left after 10 minutes, having not drunk anything, and when I complained at reception, we were distractedly told it was “service at the bar”. Firstly, the server could have told us this. Secondly, this isn’t good enough at a supposed high-class hotel where you can pay over CHF 40 a cocktail.\n\nUltimately, it only gets three stars from me because the breakfast is excellent and the staff there fantastic, and the female receptionist who checked us in and out was also really pleasant.\n\nWe live locally but it’s unlikely we’ll ever come back here. This place needs to get its act together, but nonetheless will continue to receive a steady stream of international tourists.","time":"3 weeks ago"}]'::jsonb,
