{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0dolzs6f6zqiSaPBfkn-0iubnJgqzhZgee8OdKPUofsQoCQxetd6jx5zu0QyNrIgCTuJ-EJ0QhMTxe5P0Ks34fFGAnreKP_ZVjBbREV7sn6IkRoJ8BG8i9TCeLFglKMsObUf1_F0ttfqo9SFrYfL_Oh8yvhoKgm_5nICebnf1CR5GUX0A2Glcn19WYQyoF2rwjD-kQkTOjbZlXUq9453KpSsNhX47gSP7dUzjRUfgBmHdwYyToSqjkhTiD_9WBLHY3QG0xRzB3Txa6hwOf17xr4VVs2lHBzjSqkGBClHFqOg","width":4430,"height":2953,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/117564862905264424923\">Hotel Villa Honegg</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2TjnW-x-IG_nMKaq2Z0PK_c2dgcIXGNCeum5eugHYyICMGMFb1262AzLDSty0mx3DBqCezJKisZm2MWDOyD-flMl8duf5X8ldaGS90ODMmhGXoM8EWREGNrx2j69w7fNaYbPSw9FksIBMo41fV8o3vLZVUtqwKyxSlEG3DS3BJVt9T8Ha-a6DhxiQx6_TCPnm_6vu-tyLoaEYj3IOFFQsm9RUFp8rdupO6Py-5ziQrOXvLFGHLDmpqmKt9Qmgo9QxRCUEulTbZ4-19YXjTRAmiipRQucMbDS-zBGUI7Hv5Aw","width":4800,"height":3199,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/117564862905264424923\">Hotel Villa Honegg</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Chris","rating":5,"text":"We were fortunate to host our wedding at Honegg which was an absolute dream!\n\n* Setting: Jaw dropping. Nothing else compares.\n* Hotel: While the hotel is a bit dated, it still is charming and very comfortable. The patio, terrace & pool area are perfect, my only regret was we didn''t do a \"pool party\" one night which they offer.\n* Food: Delicious & fresh, I still think about the garden salad :)\nService: Perfect without being stuffy, they clearly cared about making our experience special.\n* Coordination: Laura was an all-star, cannot recommend her enough, you should use her exclusively for all your planning work, no need for a 3rd party planner.\n* Privacy: Exceptional, you truly have your own mountaintop to yourself.\n* Cost: Definitely excessive but reasonable for how nice it is. Prepare to spend 2x what you initially expect.\n* Misc: If you have over ~70 people, you need to rent an outdoor tent and a number of other things which will greatly increase your cost but the tent worked out perfectly. Coordinate the helicopter ride from the hotel :) We did some events at Burgenstock - a gorgeous hotel and (even better) spa, but Burgenstock lacks the privacy and warmness of Honegg, also their wedding coordination people were very disorganized. Get them to have a few more clothes irons!\n\nIt''s such a special place, I miss it and can''t wait to go back!","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Frederick Quijano","rating":5,"text":"As soon as we ascended up the mountain to Hotel Villa Honegg, I knew we were entering a special place. The views were absolutely breathtaking, and the sense of peace was immediate.\n\nCheck-in was smooth, even though our room wasn’t quite ready. The reception team kindly gave us a hiking map, which made our first Swiss hike less daunting. The trail was challenging but rewarding, and our young girls powered through with endless energy. By the time we returned, our room was ready, and we were given a tour of the facilities before being shown to our stunning room. The views from our patio looked straight out of a movie.\n\nOur daughters adored the infinity pool, while my wife and I enjoyed the spa amenities. Dining was another highlight — both the restaurant and room service were superb, with food that tasted fresh, clean, and refined. A particularly memorable touch was the private theatre, which guests can book for two hours. After our hike, it was the perfect way to relax together as a family.\n\nAnother small but wonderful detail was the hotel’s postcards, featuring beautiful images of the property. Our girls loved writing and sending them to family and friends back home.\n\nThe only downside was that we stayed just two nights before moving on to our next city. We’ll absolutely return, but next time for a full week. This is the perfect place if you want to splurge and treat yourself — highly recommended.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"January Kim","rating":5,"text":"We are a 30-something couple from the US and usually stay at Marriott hotels because of status and they tend to be clean, contemporary, and usually central to touristy sights! We go off our usual Marriott hotel for special splurges at unique hotels, like the Villa Honegg!  We were here for a short stay at one of the first floor rooms with a private terrace. We loved the luxurious French villa style feel and the amazing views! I liked that there isn''t a bar inside the hotel and the sole dining area that''s by reservation only, so the hotel is very quiet. We had the formal dinner one night, which was very good, but preferred the room service food and dining on our private terrace (we liked the food better with pasta, fries, and a sandwich and we were paying for our terrace view anyway). We also got the massages which wasn''t all that special.  The infinity pool has amazing views during daytime and the evening - definitely a big perk to a stay here.  Delicious breakfast included - you can order your custom breakfast menu plus a buffet style of cold items available as well.\n\nWe didn''t have a car so we took a train from Lucerne train station to a bus station down the hill from the hotel. Then the hotel shuttle will come pick you up whenever you call for it.  Same for our return trip.\n\nService was awesome - thanks to everyone who made our stay great!\n\nDownside is there are a bazillion flies!!! Please get some sort of fly trap for inside dining room because I had to fight off the flies sitting on my food during dinner.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Jetset Bless","rating":5,"text":"Hotel Villa Honegg is an absolutely stunning 5-star retreat perched high in the Swiss mountains. From the breathtaking views to the amazing food and a spa experience that’s simply to die for, every detail exudes luxury and relaxation.\n\nFair warning — the drive up the winding, curvy mountain roads is intense and not for the faint of heart, but once you arrive, it’s all worth it. The combination of phenomenal service, exquisite design, and unforgettable ambiance makes this an experience you’ll never forget. 🏔️","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"John Foo","rating":5,"text":"It’s a top-notch hotel, comparable to St. Regis in terms of quality, personalisation and service.\n\nThe property is very well maintained, and the staff provide excellent hospitality throughout. The complimentary shuttle and the team’s remarkable attention to detail, special arrangements for us made our stay truly memorable. It’s an unforgettable experience, the view is relaxing, scenic, and peaceful. We will definitely be returning again with our family in the future.","time":"3 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
