2-6 Dec 2025, What truly elevated our stay was the excellent, seamless service across every department. The housekeeping team was meticulous and thoughtful. The dining staff was attentive and charming. And the concierge team was incredibly knowledgeable.\n\nThe location was ideal for exploring, but we often found ourselves wanting to return to the hotel just to enjoy its ambiance and that incredible view. We will be dreaming of this trip until we can return. Highest possible recommendation!","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Charlie Goodacre","rating":5,"text":"We had a fantastic stay. The hotel is beautiful, with stylish rooms, very comfortable amenities, and amazing views of the lake and mountains. Communication with the team was excellent from the moment we booked, and everything felt very smooth from check in through to check out, with some thoughtful personal touches along the way.\n\nBreakfast was lovely with a good range of fresh and a la carte options, and we really appreciated the small gifts left in our room which made the experience feel that bit more special.\n\nA special thank you to Johannes who was incredibly helpful throughout our stay. The concierge team provided great recommendations and kindly assisted with restaurant bookings, activities in Lucerne, and even our onward travel arrangements.\n\nWe thoroughly enjoyed our time here and look forward to returning.\n\nCharlie","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"karan master","rating":5,"text":"We really enjoyed MO Luzern. The location is perfect and has the most magical view and would highly recommend taking a room facing the lake. We were travelling with our pet and right from the check in, she was just completely spoiled with greetings and treats from front desk. The hotel had setup a water bowl, bed and treats for her and they even had a small roadmap for places to explore if you are travelling with a pet. Would highly recommend if you are travelling with a pet. The in-room service service was quick and responsive which made us feel warm and comfortable.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Ellaine C","rating":5,"text":"We had a lovely experience staying at Mandarin Oriental Luzern. We stayed there at the start of November, when the city wasn’t busy. The staff at the restaurant were amazing, at breakfast Adi took well care of us, and at dinner also the staff were great at Mozern! The room is clean with a lovely view of the lake. They also took care of making a huge extra bed for my 10yoson, which is a very nice detail as he felt very much taken care of.","time":"a month ago"}]'::jsonb,
