auB263t7RPZI4Tkuiqs7R2A5fZQ0b-ZjpbXK3Q8tr1_NETUcEZD138bpQhhRuO9SjODFnQG9e1oQHhL0xskFVKMDtBsZ7x2tP2Sgho0dFg8maHD7eb5Byjj-LE6lvnBu4GvbAeKQTXIg","width":2700,"height":1800,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/100469346424828090297\">Hotel Schweizerhof Luzern</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0YJ8Xq2NcHisoHQ3nvsonB48V6eQeXgjw3aPKGZe6DwcsUYDIOMd-EyUBIuqJE4Kwm99eixJWT1lsHeog2MaU5-dhWI7yo7amksqZOntOw4fqbtaY2zEyf0RrcWhROf1IRhTpX9WZX3ubx6ETfGFYQTyliYESbU9auVkbOT1du1FrqGR-KR8rSETBensfsB7SWawlvr8fxVuuYPzT0yGjHu4YvNFpqk5T6C8Fk7sNjOneOtgGWQ_SPC1vrNYO7YOyX2vMUfoM5CJBYHHofZCR2WMjyjiMvl2XMnusaUffcVg","width":1024,"height":576,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/100469346424828090297\">Hotel Schweizerhof Luzern</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Gloria Peretz","rating":5,"text":"We stayed here as part of our AMA Waterways cruise .Our room was large, elegant and comfortably furnished, overlooking Lake Lucerne. The staff was helpful and friendly. Breakfast was included and delicious. Location was perfect- we walked everywhere. Sadly, , we only  stayed 2 nights. But we will try to return someday.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Sd","rating":5,"text":"I recently chose to stay this hotel through amex platinum. I did not get the earlier room request, but Christmas holidays are busy season. Hotel provided us complimentary drink cards. our stay was wonderful. I like the fact that how family owned hotel has preserved and maintain the old charm and accommodated modern touch in rooms including the bathrooms. I highly recommend this hotel.","time":"3 weeks ago"},{"author":"lkulrich1","rating":5,"text":"We stayed here after our Viking river cruise. The location was fantastic but the best part is the staff.\nThe concierge desk helped us with a forgotten bag. They really go above and beyond. Everyone is so kind.\nYou will not regret staying here. Hotel and rooms are beautiful.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Rodica Camelia Iliescu","rating":5,"text":"We spent two unforgettable nights at Hotel Schweizerhof Luzern over New Year, including the New Year’s Eve Gala Dinner, and everything was absolutely stunning.\n\nFrom the beautiful lakefront location to the elegant room, outstanding service, and incredible atmosphere, every detail was perfect. The gala dinner was spectacular — delicious food, wonderful ambiance, and flawless organisation.\n\nThe staff were warm, professional, and genuinely welcoming, and dinner on New Year’s Day was the perfect finish to a magical stay.\n\nA truly world-class hotel — we cannot wait to return.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Amy Klucher","rating":5,"text":"Beautiful hotel on the shore of Lake Lucerne. We stayed for two nights and enjoyed the hotel breakfast buffet; there were lots of different food options for breakfast. The hotel bar is very cozy and we enjoyed a few drinks with friends after dinner. The rooms were very nice and spacious and the bathroom was fabulous with a huge shower. We highly recommend Hotel Schweizerhof when staying in Lucerne.","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
