X_7RWjHrkGQ2LSkjJVh3JcYcK6wkwMml802u7n0EpeEFPOU-3SRnwOFbxvzXpyUoOi4Vv1ASzSR-xokRJpsVLYF-kOBMvXvPROHQ8vigp929zfaecb8Q","width":1024,"height":683,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/115941659741815162952\">ART DECO HOTEL MONTANA</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2wb7XyFBjpQBS3B2euk1UmyVUhbdUIBVJcvOfNYj9aPlPCbn18GXV_dMCk11dwM_qBiKeqA8j7T1QAZjWVmtmW5Ct7uYx_Ni7Y3Mj0detJXsHVrNmXxBKfZ-oejppLccMDcTYRwK6ulI4X4aOiYITRf7DPppaDkvOFnQxmWuPbIxyQwq92AOdmvc7aN7n88NFlxzUNvdZ5SH-xW3zO8Si6nJCxHUk2ku2IEeijHTDuhtVd4XksNhoTuKZjyf3P3iRw10alRZs0uHP84UoJwEFDxTCfXbpAsYu_bW78l9P3uQ","width":1024,"height":683,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/115941659741815162952\">ART DECO HOTEL MONTANA</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Natalie Tien","rating":5,"text":"Hotel Montana in Lucerne was an absolute highlight of my stay. The view over the lake is breathtaking and the location is conveniently close to the city center.\nThe rooms are beautifully designed and very comfortable.\nThe service was exceptional throughout my stay. The staff were attentive, professional, and genuinely welcoming, always ready to help with recommendations or small requests. From check-in to check-out, everything felt seamless.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Eveline Rossi-Jackson","rating":5,"text":"Warm Welcome, Top Service & A Fabulous Room 404\nWe spent two nights at the Montana Hotel Luzern and were genuinely impressed. From the first moment, the staff were exceptionally friendly and made us feel truly welcome.\n\nOur room, 404, was fabulous – comfortable, quiet and with that “feel-good” factor you hope for on a short break. Breakfast in the room was excellent, and we were amazed that the team remembered our order perfectly the next morning. Very professional and attentive service.\n\nLunch in the restaurant was top quality, both in terms of food and atmosphere. The only small minus was the bar snack (fritto misto), which was not quite on the same level as everything else we experienced – but the kindness of the staff and the rest of the culinary offering clearly outweighed this.\n\nOverall, a wonderful stay in Lucerne. We would happily return and can highly recommend the Montana Hotel. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Carlos Arturo Perez","rating":5,"text":"Montana Art Deco is truly special. Boris at the concierge was outstanding — incredibly attentive and thoughtful. He arranged everything for us: transportation, restaurants, tours, and even concert tickets. The hotel has the most beautiful views in Lucerne, stunning rooms with terraces, and it’s an easy walk to the Old Town. Breakfast is absolutely amazing, and the bar drinks are just as good. We will definitely be back.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Amar Amin","rating":5,"text":"My recent stay at Hotel Montana in Lucerne was nothing short of outstanding. From the moment we arrived, the service, warmth, and attention to detail truly set this hotel apart — but what made our experience exceptional was the incredible support from the concierge, Boris.\n\nAs a disabled traveler, planning activities can often be challenging, but Boris went above and beyond to ensure every part of our trip was smooth, enjoyable, and fully accessible. He took the time each day to understand our needs, offered thoughtful suggestions, and curated activities that I could comfortably participate in. His kindness, patience, and deep knowledge of the area made a tremendous difference in our visit. We were able to experience Lucerne in the best possible way thanks to him.\n\nThe hotel itself is beautiful with stunning views, comfortable rooms, and a welcoming atmosphere. But it’s truly the exceptional staff — especially Boris — who elevate the experience to another level.\n\nI highly recommend Hotel Montana Lucerne to anyone visiting the area, especially travelers who appreciate personalized care and genuine hospitality. We will definitely be returning on our next trip to Switzerland.\n\nThank you again, Boris, for making our stay unforgettable.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Debbie Biswas","rating":5,"text":"The views from this hotel are stunning. I got a corner room with two balconies and waking up to the view of the mountains and the lake was heavenly.\nRooms are spacious, clean and mostly quiet. The staff is also very friendly.\nThis hotel is on top of a hill and the good thing is they have a funicular that connects it to the lake.\nIf I am ever back in Lucerne I’d be def staying here. I was also traveling solo, so felt very safe and taken care of","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
