ery happy to enjoy a restful weekend in this iconic place.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Gerrit Smit","rating":5,"text":"Arrived on Christmas day for 4 nights. We had a great time, with excellent service. Their pool & spa was heaven. Dinner was great, but pricy, regardless which restaurant you went.\nOne complete Mango, cut in slices as a dessert for CHF28,- cannot be explained.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Roksana Gh","rating":5,"text":"I don’t even know where to start, but I truly have to thank each and every one of the team members at Bürgenstock Resort for making our stay so memorable.\nI planned this trip to celebrate my partner’s birthday and wanted to organize a surprise for him. From the very beginning, the Guest Experience Team, especially Fabio and Carla, supported me with every detail ,from the room decoration to the full plan , all perfectly arranged before our arrival. Because of them, I didn’t feel stressed at all. They truly represent the real meaning of luxury hospitality.\nUpon check-in, Tony assisted us with our luggage and gave us a lovely tour of the room. Throughout our stay, he checked in on us to make sure everything was perfect and shared great recommendations about the resort and nearby activities.\nOn the day of our departure, Aitor from the front desk went above and beyond by helping us book a table at Spices Terrace and arranging our shuttle ride , the check-out process was smooth and warm, leaving us with the best final impression.\nFrom the pre-arrival planning to our last moments at the resort, everyone made us feel so special. The whole team listened carefully to what I wanted, and the results were even better than I expected. Thank you all once again for making my partner’s birthday celebration truly unforgettable. We can’t wait to come back!","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"guray ozen","rating":1,"text":"We came to celebrate my birthday, but the experience was anything but celebratory. The hotel couldn’t even secure a proper dinner reservation. First, they booked us a “recommended” 4-star restaurant without mentioning it was far away. We only found out after, when we were already soaked from the spa, with a small child, and no way to get there comfortably.\n\nWe asked the hotel repeatedly for any place to eat on-site, but everything was “fully booked.” The guy on the reception wasn’t even helpful. In the end, we were forced to order room service.\n\nThe next day, the situation got even worse. Despite my reservation including CHF 200 of dining credit, they told us room service didn’t count. Only after an exhausting discussion did they “make an exception.”\n\nAlso minor but annoying, if you take a child with you downstairs in the pool (not spa area), their employees come and warn you like very annoying way. Why? It’s not naked zone?\n\nEverything here is a hassle—small issues turning into big frustrations. This is absolutely not 5-star quality. I wouldn’t recommend it for a special occasion.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Alicia A","rating":4,"text":"This place is absolutely incredible, the view, the architecture, the atmosphere… everything is breathtaking. The spa is truly unforgettable, probably one of the most beautiful I’ve ever experienced.\n\nThat said, I expected a bit more personalization and attention to detail in the room experience. It’s still an exceptional stay overall, but it slightly lacks that extra touch of exclusivity you usually find in hotels of the same caliber.","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
