e3fyqF3eB0","width":2189,"height":1459,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/118168213977554097831\">Widder Hotel</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0EXgCLtOaN_TNbbiGlvivmMnwe5PwTJ6CcSs-zJJbrrmrZTJ0ehHh_njgCfFZtWy31CtkgEcReopGS41xyB9Duj6rRmBNZx_ti78zbx6mCOxxuGdRgKVO9hYhFTxT4rGta2q7O3FvZBFWq9ZFt2zJXHEGYalruVP8Vln-rJqDupo9i2hP4E9BdzLyXQgJuDu45pJEVrrSNbQupWLBfBlZNPk9lYa5E6IzXB0iC1B-68tE7Ry0HmM99l5a9NWP7vTVASbcv4w1f2YMT_g45AKqeNmBYhwAJUTQ09ZXEa3U","width":4800,"height":3200,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/118168213977554097831\">Widder Hotel</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Roy Shell","rating":5,"text":"Superb.\nThe Widder Hotel is one of those rare institutions that pays close attention to detail and operates at standards that go far beyond conventional luxury.\n\nI have been a regular guest here for several years, and what consistently sets Widder apart is the coherence of the experience - service, gastronomy and atmosphere - all work together at an exceptionally high level, without any sense of showmanship or excess.\n\nThe culinary side is particularly impressive.\nThe two-Michelin-star Widder Restaurant, led by Stefan Heilemann, is outstanding, and the fact that breakfast is served in the very same restaurant is a clear statement: there are no compromises here, even at the start of the day.\nBreakfast at Widder is truly exceptional!\n\nAt the same time, AuGust, under Tino Staub, offers a more relaxed but equally excellent culinary experience and is by no means a secondary option.\nThe quality and thoughtfulness are evident throughout.\n\nService is another defining strength. Having at least three remarkable concierges - Katharina, Christian, and Marco - all with Les Clefs d''Or, is extremely rare and speaks volumes about the hotel’s commitment to professionalism, experience, and genuine hospitality.\n\nFinally, the Widder Bar deserves special mention - an extraordinary whisky collection and award-winning bartenders make it a destination in its own right, well beyond the context of a hotel bar.\n\nWidder is a hotel that values substance over spectacle.\nAfter years as a returning guest, it remains one of the most consistently impressive and thoughtfully run hotels I know.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Suzan Von Hor","rating":5,"text":"Great location. Short walk from the railway station. So much is easily accessible and within walking distance. This was one of 8 locations during our “roam around Europe  trip.  It was the best. Warm and friendly staff. Our room was lovely. Plenty of space, good light and a view of autumn from my window. The restaurant and bar were packed but as Hotel guests,  we were quickly accommodated and the food was delicious. We enjoyed the dining room special set dinner one evening. As a retired chef myself, I so appreciated the knowledge level and interaction with the chef and waiters. These guys have hospitality down to a fine art. We love Zurich, so maybe a little biased. We’d go back in a heart beat.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Lawrence Lavery","rating":5,"text":"My wife and I stayed at the Widder during the first weekend of the Zurich Film Festival, and we had an excellent time.\n\nWe celebrated our anniversary there, and they made it very special for us.\n\nWe were even so lucky to have won a competition to attend the premiere of the film “Splitsville”. It just added an extra sparkle to the experience.\n\nThe room was excellent. The bed and bedding were great. We had a room with a terrace, which had a table and chairs on it.\n\nThe location is great, right in the centre of the old town on the western side of the Limmat.\n\nThe best part was the staff. Very friendly and helpful. A particular shout-out to Christian and Hans (I think his name is - I am posting this review about a month after staying there!), who checked us in. They were all friendly and helpful.\n\nThe only bad aspect was that we did not get to enjoy all aspects of the hotel, as we had a busy schedule while visiting Zurich that weekend. We did get to enjoy the Widder bar, which was, as always, excellent.\n\nWe hope to be back next year or sooner. And next time we hope to enjoy all the amenities the hotel has to offer. And we thoroughly recommend staying at the Widder.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Monk Monk","rating":5,"text":"Love the hotel.  My only point deducted would be the size.  Although I understand that hotel at that caliber in the center of the city, of course we can’t expect an extra size room but would love for it to be a bit more spacious.  The concierge were extremely helpful.  The location, can’t be better.  Right in the center but that also mean that car access is not an option.  The restaurant in the hotel were also great.  Love the Michelin starred restaurant, the bar also offers good food.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Frank Tybor","rating":5,"text":"Awesome hotel right in the heart of old town Zurich. Rooms are large and well appointed, the staff is amazing, and the hotel breakfast is my favorite on in the world(yes actually).\n\nOverall, the hotel has a quiet elegance that isn’t as showy is the other high end hotels of Zurich, but that makes the hotel feel quite, intimate and luxurious.\n\nThis is always my first choice for a hotel in zurich.","time":"a month ago"}]'::jsonb,
