as an absolute dream, perfectly balanced and full of flavor, and the artichokes were just as memorable. A special mention goes to Rebecca, who served us with such sweetness, care, and professionalism — she really made us feel welcome. Compliments to her and to the entire kitchen for an exceptional experience.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Raphael Sebban","rating":5,"text":"This place is really amazing. They have a stunning restaurant on top of the mountain with great food that really allows you to experience the beauty and the calm of Zermatt. Even if you don''t sleep in the hotel, go to eat in the restaurant, take a spot outside, and just enjoy the view because it is amazing.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Jeff Cockman","rating":5,"text":"Amazing resort!\nAt check in we were greeted with a glass of sparkling wine which always sets a nice tone. The room was large and comfortable and included a view of the Matterhorn. The spa areas are perfect for after a day of hiking/trekking.\nAnd a highlight was the breakfast! The make to order menu is extensive, and the self service area is equally impressive.  My only regret is we did not stay longer!\n\nTip - WhatsApp the resort and they will pick you up at the train station as it it quite the hike\nAnother Tip - there is an elevator at the station to Sunnegga which makes the walk much easier!","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
