HGi_sVVjZDSmdBZEASbSeCxaVV5bWmMf6eYFnXErmc8Z2XnPz348COwsQvFxUdLWOk7JImAdf0Gk13Q_SMOhow","width":4800,"height":3203,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/114952169219313296393\">Mont Cervin Palace</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2eHLZ3_eCswZeLBfC9qQykXPreWgplwCs44TT6UK6t598viFlPfq1oq1E6ykdhw7FVi03nLXtI1KVdvkbrIKhfHkGnhf8tZ6RcdS2NrOuy3NxvvYKolXKLfGQLCmimPJ3TPK50-h0b4vFCUrmT0D-QVcg4_A6Xis2n3I1xLvCR8Uws33AEKc-6MnjlGrxIJJtnlsdEmD0Qx-vxFPlFkiOrRTKbdm_NGwWJClWQs3IAb9TViNn0SG7LZ1B9yZBBCgv4t7BSLKDtOuoP1-aEDXiCiadgMJBCA_2yDqOR87ycNw","width":4800,"height":3203,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/114952169219313296393\">Mont Cervin Palace</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Lubomir Panov","rating":1,"text":"Second visit with my family and unfortunately a major disappointment. We were placed in a room outside the main hotel, on another street, requiring a long walk through a tunnel just to reach the hotel facilities. We did not feel like guests of Mont Cervin Palace, but more like we had rented an apartment elsewhere.\n\nFor the price paid, this felt misleading and not in line with the Mont Cervin Palace brand. We raised the issue with reception, but nothing meaningful was done. Very disappointing experience.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Scott Lee","rating":5,"text":"I have stayed in many hotels, but I have never felt so overwhelmed and genuinely special as I did at Mont Cervin Palace.\n\nThis isn’t just about having five-star facilities,  it’s about having true five-star staff. From the moment we arrived, every detail was perfect: the warm welcome with wine and treats, the complimentary soft drinks in the fridge, the way breakfast was beautifully organised, and how every staff member always greeted us with a smile and a “hello.”\n\nIt’s those small touches that make such a big difference, and throughout our stay my family and I could not stop raving about the service and the atmosphere here. Everything felt effortless, warm, and truly memorable.\n\nI honestly can’t wait to come back again, especially in winter, to experience it all over again. Mont Cervin Palace is easily one of the most remarkable hotel experiences I have had and one I will never forget.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Alice Chan","rating":2,"text":"We stayed here at the end of August. We were told in advance that a driver would be waiting for us at Zermatt train station and that the hotel’s red e-cars would be easy to spot. However, when we arrived, there was no one there. After waiting for a while, we decided to walk to the hotel ourselves with our luggages, only to find the pickup car parked right outside the hotel entrance.\n\nWhen I mentioned this to the staff at reception, instead of an apology, I was told rather bluntly, “You should’ve called us.” Not everyone has free international calling, and I wouldn’t expect this kind of response, or lack of responsibility, from a 5-star hotel.\n\nThat said, once checked in, service requests in the room were handled promptly, which I appreciated. But the arrival experience and the staff’s attitude at check-in really left a poor first impression.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Mario Caruso","rating":5,"text":"Very central location, perfect for exploring Zermatt. The spa is well designed and a great place to relax after a day out. Bathrooms are spacious and nicely done, adding real comfort. The Grill Restaurant is excellent, with delicious food and a warm atmosphere.\n\nSpecial mention to Jean Charles Hänggi, Bruce, and Julia for their outstanding service.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"guy domett","rating":4,"text":"This hotel is right in the centre of the village and it is only a ten minute walk from the railway station. There is good space to sit indoors and outdoors, and the wifi worked well.\nOur room had a lot of furniture so we struggled to find space to put two suitcases. The room was also fairly dark and warm at night (even with a window open). The shower is very sophisticated with a digital temperature control.\nBreakfast was good with plenty of options.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
