d personable care. We felt very welcomed and appreciated.\n\nThere is nothing I could ask or add for our hotel stay. There was even a horse drawn car carriage for transportation to and from the hotel to the train station.\n\nBreakfast was excellent and nothing fell short in our stay at the Grand Hotel Zermatterhof. Highly recommended.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Riley Hunzeker","rating":1,"text":"Deeply disappointing and frankly unacceptable experience with the reception at the hotel and their restaurant Say Cheese.\n\nWe arrived on time for our 8:30pm reservation for a party of five during New Year’s Eve week in Zermatt, a reservation that had been booked over 2.5 months in advance. Upon arrival, the hostess was dismissive and insisted—quite rudely—that no reservation existed under any of our names or under our hotel concierge’s name.\n\nOur hotel concierge immediately called the restaurant to resolve the issue. Despite this, the staff remained adamant that we did not have a reservation. At the same time, they acknowledged they had a “no-show” reservation for a party of five at the exact same time, yet still refused to seat us—despite the obvious conclusion that it was ours. We stood there for over 30 minutes trying to resolve their mistake.\n\nEventually, with no resolution and no willingness to accommodate us, we were forced to leave and find another restaurant on one of the busiest weeks of the year.\n\nTo make matters worse, we were then charged a 500 CHF cancellation/no-show fee on our card. The following day, Say Cheese refused to refund the charge, even though they themselves refused to seat us. Instead, they blamed TheFork and their “name system,” as if that absolves them of responsibility.\n\nCharging guests for a no-show when they physically showed up, argued for half an hour, and were turned away is indefensible. At minimum, this should have resulted in a full refund and a sincere apology. The fact that no compensation was offered—no refund, no meal, no goodwill gesture—speaks volumes about how this establishment treats its guests.\n\nZermatt has many excellent restaurants. Unfortunately, Say Cheese is not one of them, and I would strongly caution others against booking here, especially during peak season.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Bebee S","rating":5,"text":"The hotel provides excellent service. Personally, I think this is one of the best-service hotels I''ve ever been to in Europe, and all the staff are very nice.\n\nThe room is spacious, clean, and well-organized, and the balcony is so lovely that I couldn''t resist taking pictures.😆 Most importantly, you can see the Matterhorn from the window. Love it!!","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Real Zhen","rating":5,"text":"Best service specially Lana from reception as soon as we checked in they upgraded our room to the view of Matterhorn and when we were  checking out we informed them that we will have our train at 7 and we have a couple of hours to kill and they offered us to go to the spa which was really nice of them also our server Tania from breakfast was super nice and polite and had a fun conversation with us overall great experience 10/10 will recommend . Thank you so much!😁","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
