el’s design is unique and every detail reflects the use of high-end materials, creating a truly luxurious atmosphere.\nIdeal for all types of guests — couples, families, and anyone looking for a special experience. Definitely worth visiting!\n\nWe stayed in a Deluxe Room: spacious, with a balcony, modern facilities, an iPad to control lights and curtains, a cozy fireplace, and a large bathroom with a perfect shower cabin. The mattresses were incredibly comfortable, and housekeeping team is super professional.\n\nAmazing Spa: Olympic-size pool, heated outdoor pool, family zone, and a 16+ area with pools, saunas, and hammams.\n\nBreakfast offered a wide variety of choices, buffet and hot dishes, all served with friendly and efficient service.\n\nHighly recommended!","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Romain S","rating":4,"text":"Chedi is a very frustrating hotel, mixing the best with some very average side.\nIt features everything you are looking for in such luxury hotel but misses true luxury spirit.\nThe rooms are definitely the highlight, big, great view, well decorated & cozy, with a lot of great details (even if I have the impression it is starting to be less and less good). The spa is great and big in terms of surface but WAY to small if the hotel is full. I tried all restaurants including the Michelin stars Japanese and they all feel good but very average, definitely not to the level of such hotel.\nThe common areas are big but lack spirit and luxury touches. The service is good but not mind blowing, miles away from the best hotels on the planet.\nOverall Chedi is a nice hotel, well located with a lot of great facilities. However I do not recommend to go over the weekend as it is a very annoying hotel when it is full, feeling a bit like a factory.\nThis hotel is super premium, but not very luxurious in my opinion.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Charlotte Grüter","rating":5,"text":"Everything was absolutely perfect. From the warm welcome at reception to the impeccable service throughout our stay, The Chedi Andermatt exceeded every expectation. The food was outstanding, the spa was world-class, and every detail was handled with genuine care. Housekeeping was also absolutely perfect.\n\nA special mention goes to Salvatore, the exceptional restaurant manager who truly went above and beyond. As two hoteliers at heart, we can confidently say that he embodies the true soul of hospitality. His professionalism, warmth, and passion elevated our entire experience. This is exactly what 5-star service is and what it should always aspire to be.\n\nThank you for an unforgettable stay. We will be back.","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
