d well-curated events throughout the year.\n\nWith an on-site ski shop and wardrobe, elegant boutiques, and a hair salon, every detail is thoughtfully covered. That’s exactly why it’s called a Palace—always exciting!\nThank you Gstaad Palace!","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Derryl","rating":5,"text":"My two-week accommodation was a pleasant and rejuvenating experience, with spectacular views. The meals were exquisitely crafted to suit the palate. I extend my gratitude and warm regards.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"fafar101","rating":5,"text":"Memorable place to stay at. Service and staff is over the top nice. They spoil you to the max. A beautiful postcard like place I never forget. Picturesque and serene. Would return a 100 times. Love, love, love!!!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Scott Bannister","rating":5,"text":"I have been fortunate to stay at the Palace multiple times over the past seven years, and each visit somehow manages to surpass the last. From the moment you arrive, the hotel team greets you with such genuine warmth that you instantly feel at home. Their attention to detail and kindness truly set the tone for a memorable stay.\n\nThe rooms are always immaculate and beautifully decorated. I especially appreciate the spacious lounge, the comfortable bed, and the wonderful  bathroom, everything I need to unwind whilst away from home.\n\nOne of the standout features for me is the food. It is consistently exceptional, with a wide variety of beautifully prepared dishes. As someone with coeliac disease, I am particularly grateful for how well the menu accommodates my gluten-free requirements. I have never had to worry about what I can eat - the staff are knowledgeable and always go out of their way to ensure I feel safe and well taken care of.\n\nThe Palace has truly become a home away from home for me, and I cannot recommend it highly enough. Whether it is your first visit or your tenth, you can always expect exceptional service, incredible comfort, and a genuinely welcoming atmosphere.","time":"6 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
