fectly timed refreshment, a handwritten note, or the way the staff remembered our preferences.\n\nThe rooms are not only luxurious, but also incredibly cozy, with stunning views and touches that make you feel both pampered and at home. The spa is a sanctuary, the restaurants are world-class, and the atmosphere throughout the hotel is serene yet sophisticated.\n\nThis is one of the rare places where five stars truly mean something. The Alpina Gstaad doesn’t just meet expectations — it exceeds them at every level. We left feeling genuinely taken care of, and already can’t wait to return.\n\nA heartfelt thank you to the entire team — you’ve created something truly special.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Charlotte Frazier","rating":5,"text":"Stunning hotel with magical views. The staff are very helpful and enjoy their work. They can''t do enough for you. The location is amazing, and there is a shuttle service that will drop you off and pick you up in town. That can easily fit a buggy in without taking it down. The kids club is wonderful well equipped but opens late 11 and closes late 9pm 9.30- 7pm would be better hours for the children they cater to in my opinion, and Angela is very kind and caring and does a fantastic job with all ages. There is a clean and safe playground and a cinema room that can be booked out.\n\nIt''s a child friendly place but designed around adults'' enjoyment. The spa is beautiful and the facilities are perfect for a romantic relaxing stay.\n\nThe food is perfect. Every meal is delicious, especially the lobtser at the buffet bbq, and the dim sum at breakfast, which sadly I left trying till near the end of our visit.\n\nThe beds are very comfortable even with a bad back and the rooms have everything you could want the slippers are the best I''ve ever experienced at a hotel and make you feel right at home.\n\nI would live here if I could it''s that good.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Nico Isapro","rating":5,"text":"We went to the day spa there, for 140 CHF.\nThe service is one of the best I encountered so far, it’s definitely more than 5 stars.\nThe changing rooms were very luxurious and there was everything you might need there.\nThe pools are nice especially the outside one.\nIt was calm and relaxing.\nWe also took a drink at the lobby, people were playing live music and that really enhanced the experience.\nI wish I could let a comment about the rooms but unfortunately we couldn’t afford the night price 😉","time":"7 months ago"},{"author":"Andrey Yukhanaev","rating":4,"text":"Very pretentious place with a lot strange looking people acting in a vanity fair mode. The Italian restaurant left rather convoluted featuring, the food was not up to par for the prices charged, service guys needs also a bit more training, maybe because it just opened.","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
