ps://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/104661776877358433664\">Lenkerhof gourmet spa resort - Relais &amp; Châteaux</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0vUBvmWvPfVA4Bb5Vx73UpyS25VDxzYufou_ZwrkJIr5OAN5RvmhKLTQR6BAJIOIw9xjvTtJk9QDBIpou6xk5L2xjM7p2-6x0sgsHsMYKTaa_p0-tVlsBvc-bJilq3AOoG1tN7eHdFuIlKiXqZrTyVycTdRktaL2isB5C5XX3r-PDtrGKP4q-vwukhCcgYAnufr0tZvVsa-q9LOm9L2hDjDyZKPw7ZGLxS_99A0jrbokoD3tN53buTDF9jSBP8efp6HI0_S8nONCv5MQ1qmGLLRLwKyL8Kh-6Fcr9P4zcGtg","width":2500,"height":1667,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/104661776877358433664\">Lenkerhof gourmet spa resort - Relais &amp; Châteaux</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN3nnqm7GQkNi2JBxQfMLxiORIoS2pU7Dw6Gkfsr6YMaChksez6XQUgnXzusZsWFj0S_zvIBUBPNJJE81k-CFcUh_IPCPQr2-rtYonQipptTXR5qKwHGN3EfFQDklzZQKtUFixxSM5fc9rVfRHbo5F-a3hIDlnwzPpxXX9z1QSn5d6gaz4737B4BHQ-Ot5zOTiY8G8JMd_GFSc4RupPF9Dt0-7EBO1qrQiLoYgBWFdYNg8nZZkU8dAVhhrZ96aeySGS3xjxC-rlku_RCMZx8JPs8jgphMCEL0g-2kHit_K10LA","width":4800,"height":3200,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/104661776877358433664\">Lenkerhof gourmet spa resort - Relais &amp; Châteaux</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Monica Rackley","rating":5,"text":"We absolutely loved our stay at Lenkerhof over Christmas. The hotel was so beautiful and staff were so friendly and couldn’t do enough to help us. They have a Christmas program to help celebrate Christmas and make it a bit more special. It is very close to the ski resorts and winter hiking trails so there is lots to do. We travelled with our daughter and they were so welcome to her with kids activities and a  Christmas present. Their on site restaurants were innovative and delicious.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Rachel Walker","rating":5,"text":"About 15 minute walk away from the train station but if you arrange staff will happily pick you up. Lenk ski lift right next to the hotel. Overall a very decent stay, most of the staff were very nice however there was this one woman at the reception who was very rude and passive aggressive. The views from our room were extraordinary. Also if anyone plans on ordering room service the menu they have in the rooms is a small version, if you ask for the full room service menu they’ll bring it. Very worth it has a lot more nice food","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Alex D","rating":5,"text":"You could argue that the hotel is slightly dated in design, but the service was absolute perfection from start to finish. True hospitality without any pretention but with all the attention to detail.\nThe bread at breakfast was a tiny bit disappointing, stale and a bit uninspired - the wonderful view and delicious prepared warm food deserve a better bread offering to go with!","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Lily Fantoni","rating":1,"text":"We waited 1 hour and 20 minutes for two starters, and then another 30 minutes for a simple limoncello — which I had to ask for again 10 minutes later.\nThe food and wine were actually good, and the Spanish and Greek waiters were kind, but the overall service was just painfully slow.\nIt completely ruined the experience and made me feel disrespected as a guest.\nI’m staying at the hotel tonight — maybe things will improve — but for now, it’s a big no.\n\nUPDATE after the full stay:\nUnfortunately, things only got worse after dinner.\n\nBefore booking, we called the hotel to ask if any construction work would affect the stay, and we were told nothing about noise or disturbance. Yet the next morning, construction started at 9:30 a.m., with loud noise in the room.\n\nThe bathroom layout is very poor, and having carpet on the bathroom floor is simply unhygienic for any hotel, let alone one claiming 5 stars.\n\nAt dinner, we had already waited 1h20 for two starters and had to ask for water three times over 20 minutes before it finally arrived. Even the table next to us commented on how badly we were being treated. Later, when paying, we were first given a wrong bill that charged us more than what we ordered, which was corrected immediately after we checked the bill ourselves, they then offered us coffees and a limoncello as a gesture.\n\nThe spa area is far below any luxury standard: no robes, no cotton pads, only one toilet, towels to be collected at reception, and used sanitary paper left in the changing room. The sauna literally overlooks the construction site and workers (see photos).\n\nFinally, during check-out, we were told that if we wanted a spa gesture, we would need to remove our Google review. That kind of pressure is absolutely unacceptable and unprofessional.\n\nAt 450 CHF per night, this is nowhere near a 5-star experience. I came here to rest and left exhausted and disappointed.\n\nThat said, I want to sincerely thank the three kind waiters from the restaurant and the lovely receptionist who were genuinely attentive and warm throughout our stay. The issue clearly comes from management and organization, not from the staff themselves, who were doing their best.\n\nI’ve attached photos of the sauna view and the waste left in the changing area as proof.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Yildiz de Leeuw","rating":2,"text":"We visited the day spa as external guests and the experience was very disappointing. We arrived at 15:00, clearly mentioned that we would only be using the textile section of the spa and had to pay the full day rate for the entire spa. We paid CHF 136 for two people. The textile sauna area consists of just two very small saunas and one slightly larger one. The spa felt extremely limited, and we were done after barely an hour because there simply wasn’t much to do or explore. This experience felt underwhelming, outdated and absolutely not worth the money.","time":"a month ago"}]'::jsonb,
