 as always! As local summer residents, we are very happy members of the Palace Spa and Gym facilities. My highest praise to their outstanding team: The very precise and caring Patrizia, Emanuele (who has tremendously positive team spirit!), the very thoughtful and kind Silvio, the swift and friendly Matteo, the intelligent, bright and engaging Ava, and of course the very lovely and beautiful Ioanna, Julianna, Sandra, and Mara. At La Diala, Diogo is always so incredibly professional and courteous, Antonio and Signor Maurizio and the junior staff are also very helpful. The team at the spa and make coming to the Palace everyday such a delight — their utmost professionalism, thoughtfulness, and genuine joie de vivre and care truly distinguishes the property, and I cannot sing their praises enough. Many thanks also to Emma from housekeeping, the very kind bellmen (Signor Gianpiero) and the warm concierge team, and dear Giulia at the Gelateria — home to many scoops of happiness, thanks to Chef Stefan''s creativity and Giulia''s kindness. We are also very impressed with the culinary team and FOH service at Il Paradiso. Excellence abounds, and we are so grateful.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Shahad S","rating":5,"text":"Badrutt’s Palace in St. Moritz is absolutely stunning! One of the most beautiful hotels I’ve ever stayed in, with flawless service and every corner exuding luxury and elegance. Truly an unforgettable experience 😍","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Sumaia A.","rating":5,"text":"I tried both their rooms and suites, and both are nice, but of course, if you can afford the St. Moritz suite, then it''s the best. The hotel is luxurious and has a stunning view. They have a high-quality spa, swimming pool, gym, and playground for children. However, for couples, be prepared to hear children crying at night and early morning. The second floor smells weird; I thought it was the smell of an old house, but when I moved to the 4th floor, there was no smell. Housekeeping can be hard to reach, but if you''re staying in a suite, you don''t need to worry - you''ll get all the attention you want and more. The food is good, but not consistent; I guess it depends on who takes the order and who''s the chef for the day. Despite this, I loved the hotel and will definitely come back.","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
