5486660420448\">Grand Hotel Des Bains Kempinski St. Moritz</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2T6Ty_2sIPfbe24XTqd0kwHg-YL0pptKDU6_pY3957i7FkErBjB2TV4KTiG0vgzcLi29GgH8jXlz1yISDHA4ZRmQwtXpY5AhsJ9EcGkOb8QggtuJCZHzFaaNG9XKQ20bYjh-zFsm02wMhE8daKcEAnKMH1Q1GbqmyJ1SFJOjTFvNgg4wJDl2N9_-a7nKa5hVVU0ffO3sWJcmXX8647Xyj6Bq4JyC4wz8L8VclYH1bwkpO-wU8WJ04DH5ePykcsvIaU5Q_CPwIwmgSYf0YSRyuMkTCoQRZwVaZHPSy2KZ7tkg","width":3264,"height":4080,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/115022985486660420448\">Grand Hotel Des Bains Kempinski St. Moritz</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0jFqA9yvM1KzyHZVJMJSrB2rs2flWk5CRTAdFwEe_C5C12QlCbh74jfj_95wXbkOoSQuLvBV3T6GQbgWXQBkWoxjFR7CkCBelSpNrs33qS2J4oYJ8gA4Nlg-niab21Dff4GM_jUwxEv5pmISRAzIcTVOmU6feok6ScUi0acHAnRTlreQv96KeruYMXPDuibbadIQgf4UQS-p2F2-_BlUbENC9qmAqDuBCccnBsjpTiFZbqL6HOHQg_07FRsjvsdZOOsWVSeVAp9Qzz8hPF8vp3nH5ZCMhIPlFZUKi577tG0w","width":1920,"height":1080,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/115022985486660420448\">Grand Hotel Des Bains Kempinski St. Moritz</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Jeff Ifrah","rating":5,"text":"From the moment I arrived, my experience at this hotel was nothing short of exceptional. The service stood out immediately—warm, attentive, and genuinely committed to making every guest feel cared for. Every staff member I interacted with went above and beyond, whether it was at check-in, in the restaurants, or throughout the property.\n\nThe property itself is stunning—beautifully maintained with an elegant yet welcoming atmosphere. Every corner, from the lobby to the outdoor spaces, reflected a consistent attention to detail that made the entire environment feel serene and luxurious.\n\nMy room exceeded expectations: spacious, spotless, and thoughtfully designed with both comfort and style in mind. The bed was incredibly comfortable, amenities were of the highest quality, and small touches (like turn-down service and personalized notes) made it feel truly special.\n\nThe spa is a highlight in itself. From the tranquil ambiance to the expert therapists, each treatment felt restorative and luxurious. It was the perfect escape for both body and mind.\n\nThe valet team was seamless and efficient—always prompt and courteous, making arrivals and departures effortless. Housekeeping also deserves praise: they maintained the room to perfection, with impeccable cleanliness and attention to detail. Every day it felt like stepping into a freshly prepared space.\n\nOverall, this hotel delivers an experience that feels both welcoming and world-class. It’s clear that excellence is woven into every aspect, from the staff’s attitude to the property’s design and upkeep. I left feeling refreshed and already look forward to returning.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Mister Spot","rating":3,"text":"Oh Kempinski, why are you so distant when normal middle class people show up at your door? Why the long faces from management? Why make us feel like dogs in a bowling alley? Perhaps we are not superficial enough? Sorry, next time we will bring disguises, long nails, more makeup, fancy shoes...\nOutrageously expensive, pretentious.\nBuy insurance as they have a no refund policy.\nExcellent included breakfast with attentive personnel. Never more than 10 persons at the breakfast, in a room that can accommodate hundreds.\nHow annoying to sit next to the lobby and hear two different types of music coming from different sources One from the lobby bar, and one from the lobby itself. Not relaxing.\nLocation is remote, like an hospital in the suburban sprawl. Nothing around, meaning restaurants or anything meaningful within walking distance. Good for pampered seclusion though.\n\nBeautiful decor, too bad some members of the personnel are judgemental.\n\nPlease do not reply or apologize, you already missed the point on \"treat every customer the best you can\".","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Claire-Jane Rewcastle","rating":5,"text":"Fabulous, relaxing week. The staff are welcoming and friendly - we had a wonderful tour on e-bikes with Alessandro & his fellow concierges (Simone & another colleague) were faultless - great recommendations, nothing was too much trouble - and great humour too! Our room was comfortable and perfectly cleaned. Breakfast was delicious - and friendly service too. The only downside: the food in the hotel in the evening looked underwhelming and pricey, so although we’d have liked to eat here in the evenings, we ate elsewhere. Overall, great hotel, lovely relaxing atmosphere and the staff are first-rate. Thank you for a wonderful stay! :)","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Pāvels Kuzmins","rating":5,"text":"Our summer stay at the Kempinski Grand Hotel des Bains in St. Moritz was simply exceptional. From the moment we arrived, the service was warm, professional, and genuinely attentive. The hotel perfectly blends traditional alpine charm with modern luxury, and the views of the Engadin valley in summer are absolutely breathtaking.\nThe room was spacious, elegantly decorated, and featured every comfort we could have hoped for. Mornings started with a delicious breakfast spread- fresh, varied, and beautifully presented. Afternoons were spent enjoying the spa and wellness facilities, which are among the best we''ve experienced!","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Karla Kutlakova","rating":5,"text":"Beautiful lakeside hotel with excellent service. The rooms are beautiful, spacious and very clean with mountain views. The breakfast was plentiful, very tasty and the staff was very attentive. The spa area is charming and very relaxing after long walks in the mountains. We enjoyed our stay and were very relaxed, we would love to return.","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
