jXTBFttptcnAtB8KaaW3yjtFvc2J-w","width":2500,"height":1667,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/118110692691888265499\">Nira Alpina</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN3Ar3hzsqKyVwxowqJx1P1Ol5y5wgWeUfwanmwNjKTzLvC0hiJL4Hp75h__nYiLrhKNpzeA9MLv1Kzbov8G2QXQCgAh__BGw7DIPHzi0t_CUhWgIz4-jZZAY-Lxkiqiw3e-IgpWdwk1nSCGCswezGu_Cl5EZok8Zxah2hKgt6FOBq6bp57Z3E6YXeS8HdHAPSFTA5xNETARWq2dwIrHvaFe4YjsKeZoLqVYl-R2r1djF4GjUv1iXMNg3RuNzOWBs7mRm5sAhhFklfeHumVSRnz66Z54EyfxdTvD_SXUaMCWig","width":2048,"height":1536,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/118110692691888265499\">Nira Alpina</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Jordan Abidor","rating":5,"text":"From the moment your train arrives in St. Moritz and Nira Alpina picks you up, you are in for a real treat. Every single employee who works here embodies true customer service and care. We enjoyed eating at Stars and the Fondue Popup on Wednesday, the massages and spa area were excellent and the staff were highly responsive and attentive. We were able to rent gear right next to the hotel and get a $47 lift pass from the front desk which made impromptu skiing easy.\n\nClaudia, the general manager, remembered every detail of every person and employee in the hotel and was genuinely thoughtful and caring at every turn of the trip. I cannot recommend this place more highly.","time":"in the last week"},{"author":"Alex","rating":5,"text":"Ideally located directly opposite the ski lift to the Corvatsch 3303 peak, the hotel preserves a warm, family-style atmosphere, with managers who remember each guest and are always ready to help. Easy access to other ski areas and St. Moritz. Spacious parking for guests. Special thanks to Giannis, whom I have known for 12 years — an exceptional professional in hotel management and genuine guest care.","time":"3 weeks ago"},{"author":"V P","rating":4,"text":"Very nice and very close to the ski slopes, if you like to be the first on the slopes and enjoy the early morning when the slopes are still \"intact\" is the hotel for you, i like it because there''s a bridge direct to the station where you can take the first gondola, unfortunately the chairlift connection to St. Moritz was closed at the time i was there, so if you want to get there you need to commute to the town if you want to enjoy all the available slopes.\n5hey have a room for kids with plenty of toys so your kids can''t get bored and a small pool so after the skiing kids can play while you rest in the pool!","time":"3 weeks ago"},{"author":"Damla Y. B.","rating":5,"text":"The restaurant staff are exceptionally friendly, helpful, and thoroughly professional. The view from the room is absolutely breathtaking, and the entire hotel exudes peace and cleanliness. The food is delicious.\n\nIf I could suggest one small improvement, it would be better regulation of the hot water in the rooms.\n\nA wonderful bonus is that the hotel is dog-friendly and genuinely thoughtful about accommodating pets. From here, you can easily take a bus to St. Moritz and other charming towns in the area, or simply hop on the funicular right inside the hotel and admire the stunning glacier at 3,033 meters.\n\nWorth every penny! thank you for a memorable experience!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Hendrine. van Walbeek","rating":5,"text":"What an amazing hotel! Not only are the rooms comfortable, tidy and big, ofcourse they all have stunning views. These views can be seen from the rooms, the bar and the restaurant.\nThe food and drinks are excellent but what made it all complete, are the people. Every single person in this hotel is kind, caring and love to help you in anyway they can. They take their time for a personal chat with us. An excellent choice for a shorter or longer stay in the Swiss mountains. We had a fantastic holiday! Thank you so much.","time":"6 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
